sandpaper” image to a reference “sandpaper only” image produces two sensitive differential phase
contrast images, giving the sample phase gradient in vertical and horizontal directions. These images
are then integrated to recover the projected phase depth of the sample. The simple experimental
set-up, retention of ﬂux, and the need for only a single sample image per reconstruction suggest that
this method is of value in imaging a range of dynamic processes at both synchrotron and laboratory
x-ray sources.},
